COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 390, L.D. 901
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the resolve.
33 It requires the Maine Redevelopment Land Bank Authority to work with the City of Bangor
44 to develop a comprehensive plan for the redevelopment of the property in the City of
55 Bangor commonly known as the Bangor Mall. The plan must include a mix of uses for the
66 property that promotes the economic revitalization of the Bangor Mall as a vital hub in the
77 City of Bangor and creates affordable housing for the city and surrounding regions. By
88 January 15, 2026, the authority must submit a report to the Joint Standing Committee on
99 Housing and Economic Development on the plan, and the committee may report out
1100 legislation based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
